sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The promoter includes the three OmpR binding sites: C1, C2, and C3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1.
An alternate version, BBa_R0083, cuts out the C2 and C3 sites.
The efficacy of this promoter versus the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) or the ompF upstream region (BBa_R0084) is currently unknown.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K116501

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The binding affinity to DNA still have to be confirmed
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chun-Ju Yang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SasA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The SasA???RpaA signal transduction system represents an activation output pathway from the cyanobacteria Kai oscillator. SasA is transfer its phosphoryl group to RpaA, which is predicted to activate this RR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The pst I enzyme site at 718bp - 723bp was mutated (CTGCAG->TTACAA). This mutated construct is convenient for us to clone in standard biobrick part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chun-Ju Yang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: KaiA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: KaiA coding region with an extra stop codon at the end and two silent mutations at the EcoRI and PstI cut sites. From Prochlorococcus (Synechococcus) elongatus PCC7942 genome. The actual DNA is synthetic in nature; was synthesized from GeneArt AG. Note that the coding region is bounded by the BioBricks Primers and is on a non-BioBrick vector pGA4 (ampR). The biobricks primers can be cut out along with the KaiA coding sequence with HindIII and SacI. Length of entire plasmid is 3802bp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhipeng Sun

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: KaiB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: KaiB coding region with an extra stop codon at the end. From Prochlorococcus (Synechococcus) elongatus PCC7942 genome. The actual DNA is synthetic in nature; was synthesized from GeneArt AG. Note that the coding region is bounded by the BioBricks Primers and is on a non-BioBrick vector pPCR-Script (ampR). The biobricks primers can be cut out along with the KaiB coding sequence with KpnI and SacI. The length of the entire plasmid is 3220bp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhipeng Sun, Hetmann Hsieh, Jeffrey Lau, David Ramos

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: KaiC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: KaiC coding region with an extra stop codon at the end. Two silent point mutations at EcoRI and PstI site. From Prochlorococcus (Synechococcus) elongatus PCC7942 genome. The actual DNA is synthetic in nature; was synthesized from GeneArt AG. Note that the coding region is bounded by the BioBricks Primers and is on a non-BioBrick vector pGA4(ampR). The biobricks primers can be cut out along with the KaiCcoding sequence with KpnI and XhoI. The length of the entire plasmid is 4558bp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhipeng Sun, Hetmann Hsieh, Jeffery Lau, Dave Ramos
